k it randomly stops? haha

so ever since I got this thing back I havent really been reflecting on my emotions and stuff like I used to, maybe because before I went to far with it and people were like blah blah..ya thats what they said but I just have so many things in my life that I keep to myself and wondering if someday I will truly be understood for who I am and what I have to offer, but I'm always just pushed away from everyone, it's like I can either try my hardest to make someone laugh or I can be a complete annoying bitch, thats who've I become and I haven't seen the person I used to be in quite some time now, this year has been complete hell, starting with the summer, for once after the big drama break up I thought things were going great, I actually wanted to get to know someone and care about them, but of course nothing ever works out and its not like im not over it cause I am, and that would be creepy if I wasn't, but sometimes it crosses my mind, I'm wondering who I am, and when will I truly be happy and ...well nice, if I didn't have my friends with me I really don't know what I would do, I can tell it's not easy to be friends with me, because I go through so much self-drama that I can't even stand myself sometimes 

so this year being hell and all ya..nobody in school is good, I miss when my sister was a senior, freshman year was the best year I ever had, all of my friends were together and it's like now theres this constant battle of who I should be friends with and who I shouldn't be, it's not that I don't wanna be friends with this one person it's just I never feel like I can fully trust them, should I just let things go and pretend I don't know what's being said about me all the time -no I used to that and I'm never going back to that, kinda like I don't think I'm ever gonna go back to the way I used to be, when I was happy and confident of myself, it's seems like everyday that goes by it gets worse and worse, I'm always in this constant battle to change myself inside and out, primarly the reason I dyed my hair red, but it's fading back thank god ha but I just craved a change in my life, wanting to be the person I'm not and most likely never will be in English were reading this book the Catcher in the Rye and for some odd reason I find myself relating to Holden, it's really creepy minus the craving for sex and complaining about people picking their pimples but seriously I feel as lonesome as he does, and how someone he's craving relationships but yah..and

I'm really not using this livejournal to catch attention from anybody, nobody is sitting down forcing you to read me bitch about my life, its your choice, but this is the closest thing I have to a person to spill my guts to, besides Anna and Ally their like my diaries that talk back but sometimes I just feel like I can't lay all my problems on them every waking moment of my life because if I had to hear me 24/7 like they did i'd kick my ass

so speaking of kicking asses, I had a basketball scrimage today and I got the ball and I'm like oh cool I have the ball and this crazy girl grunts and pushes me so hard that my chubby body knocks over and falls dramatically onto the bleachers, god that killed, I just like sat there holding myself back from running up to her blonde ass and punching her in the face, that I crave to do everyday of my life when people piss me off but I just kept going on with the "fantastic game" yah did I mention I like dove to get the ball and I skidded my body across the floor for like what seems like 5 minutes ha, pretty funny, then I punched Nicole Wimmer so hard because someone told me to haha Nicole I love you ;-)

so this brings me to the end of my day and my constant fear of running into someone at school that I can't even get the nerve to take myself out of advisement anymore, not the way it should be, but when your constantly getting told something over and over again they overpower you and get you for the best and I'm just saying this it better stop soon

your free to leave a comment of question or whatever you want- but I'm not sitting here expecting one

<3 Mandi
